            Rated 3 out of
            5
 by
        snwwhit23 from
        Batting balls up
When washed the batting inside bunch all up.Very disappointing.I had hoped this wouldn't happen with a name brand item.
Date published: 2017-05-22





            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        Anonymous from
        Very satisfied
Beautiful set. Very glad I ordered this, it even made our old brass bed look good! Good quality, soft, and generously sized. We'll have this set for many years. Thank you Scott Living and QVC
Date published: 2016-06-20





            Rated 3 out of
            5
 by
        love the mountains from
        soft but 2 pillows don't match very well
I've waited for years to buy a new bedding set for my master's bedroom and for some reason I chose this one. Probably because the Scott Brothers were so entertaining during their segment. This bedding set is very soft, no smell issues like others said at all. It is a light comforter which is perfect for this Montana home during the warmer months. The one issue I have with this is the two larger throw pillows do not really coordinate as they are more taupe and the rest of the set is more grey. I will not be using these and will look for more grey pillows to complement the rest of the set and the one pillow in front. Truly not a biggy but it would have been nice if the two pillows matched more exactly. Grey and taupe are not my idea of complementary colors. Thanks Scott Brothers though for this nice bedding set though!
Date published: 2016-06-01





            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        Joy67 from
        Absolutely beautiful!
I purchased the Biolan in the King size for a Queen size mattress. I have a thick featherbed and wanted the comforter to look like a bedspread. The fit is perfect. Living in the Southwest I wanted touches of turquoise and dark coral but I didn't want a true southwest design. The Biolan design is classy with just the right amount of color for accent. I was concerned the comforter may be too warm during the summer but with the air conditioning it's comfortable. I consider this a lightweight comforter and I'm happy with that because I hate having anything heavy on me while sleeping. I will not use the Navy throw pillows; the material is like a faux suede and doesn't look good with the set. The smaller pillow looks nice. I have white walls in my bedroom and the Biolan has a white background (hard to tell from the pictures) so this set looks like it was custom made for me. Thanks guys....good job!
Date published: 2016-05-30





            Rated 3 out of
            5
 by
        bjglace from
        Nice but underwhelming
The comforter is very pretty. Material is thin. Will need to take it off at night as our dog sleeps with us. Has a funny smell but hope it goes away since it is now out of the plastic.
Date published: 2016-05-28





            Rated 3 out of
            5
 by
        r in va from
        it's ok
The comforter's fabric is very thin. If you have a dog that lays on the bed don't get it, I am sure it will rip. I love the colors and wanted something very colorful for Summer. I was excited to get throw pillows with it but the navy background does not go with any color in the comforter. I am not using them on the bed. Yes I am a Libra and like things balanced lol! I am not sending it back but not very thrilled about it. I guess I expected more with these guys name on it but then again I guess I would be paying more too.
Date published: 2016-05-28






