Reviews & Community QA





Scott Living 3 Piece King Coverlet Set is rated
    4.3 out of
    5 by
    3.







            Rated 4 out of
            5
 by
        ncsmca from
        Great Coverlet
Love the fabric and design, I just ordered a second color, taupe to go with the coral TSV sheets. The Seaglass works well with the lattice sheets. I too am disappointed in the shams, hoping they were quilted as well - the zipper is difficult to use. It is hard to find a good quality coverlet !
Date published: 2017-07-02





            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        pageRus from
        Perfect Beautiful Coverlet
I ordered the coverlet in two colors to see which one I like better with the Seattle bedding from the Scott brothers (Which is absolutely gorgeous by the way). I got the creamy white and seablue green. Love them both but think I will keep the creamy white. I would love to keep both but can't justify doing that. The seablue green coverlet is gorgeous but doesn't exactly match the bedding as it does on the video the way I would like it too. I know you don't have to match exactly but I kind of like to. Plus my curtains are white so it ties it all together. The coverlets are fabulous quality and look expensive like hotel bedding but better. I'm now a bigger Scott brothers fan. I have ordered their comforter, coverlet, sheets and towels and all high quality at much less cost. Doing the Happy Dance for the Scott brothers!
Date published: 2017-06-29





            Rated 4 out of
            5
 by
        Anonymous from
        Shams
Received the sea glass coverlet and shams. I have a California king size bed and got the king size coverlet set and to my surprise it fit beautifully on my bed and around the sides, it's very generous. All the other coverlet sets that I've purchased in the past barely cover the sides of my bed. The shams are not quilted as the bed coverlet. They feel very much like a pillow case that's why I gave it minus one star. The cases for the pillow come with a zipper on the top or bottom depending on how you place it on the bed and it's not noticeable. They glide over nicely but you need to use both hands one to hold the other to zip. I understand that these are pillow shams but was expecting it to match the coverlet quilt at least on one side.
Date published: 2017-06-29






